reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Priced Combo
reviews.reviewText: Used for an upgrade and I am very satisfied with my purchase. The price was great and reliable as expected.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fast, working as stated but HARD to Get working
reviews.reviewText: First, you MUST update the BIOS to the latest version. A MUST! For me this motherboard is very picky with a lot of small issues. Youtube is your best friend here, just search each issue you have one at a time to see fixes with helped me a lot. I am not a expert but have built a few PC's. Once done, it seems like a nice system.NOTE: I still have one major issue and that is bluetooth. I have a bluetooth keyboard and it connects fine (MXKEYS) but as soon as you reboot the system no bluethooth devices auto reconnect. I also tried with sony x1000 headphones and same issue. You have to go and reconnect after every boot. Not sure if this is a windows 11 issue or this motherboard bluetooth issue.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars great middle expense upgrade to build your own system
reviews.reviewText: I needed an upgrade after 5 years and these were a good medium match to get me into future. I used a Corsair 4000D case and was super easy and successful. Just be careful to google bios upgrade videos and carefully follow the instructions. My video card installed covered SATA drive connectors 1 and 2, so install those cables before you install video card. Or you have to remove and reinstall it. Plenty of info out there on installation process. I kept my drives and video card, but new would not be an issue. I recommend the Samsung SSD drives, super easy with their software to transfer operation system in old drive to the Samsung. I added this new one. Yea go for it. Been years since I did my last build and very pleased with results.

reviews.reviewText: Great board everything came in great shape super pleased

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Impressive Performance and Value Bundle!
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the AMD Ryzen 5 5500 6-Core, 12-Thread Unlocked Desktop Processor Bundle, and I must say it has exceeded my expectations. This bundle offers a fantastic combination of power, efficiency, and value that makes it a great choice for both casual users and gamers.The performance of the Ryzen 5 5500 is outstanding. The 6 cores and 12 threads provide smooth multitasking, and the unlocked nature of the processor allows for easy overclocking, catering to enthusiasts who want to squeeze out even more power. Whether I'm running demanding applications or playing resource-intensive games, the processor handles everything with ease.The bundle also includes a well-designed and efficient cooling solution, which helps in maintaining optimal temperatures during prolonged usage. This is a significant plus for those who want to ensure the longevity of their system without investing in an additional cooling solution.Moreover, the price point of this bundle is highly competitive, offering excellent value for the performance it delivers. AMD has consistently proven itself in the market, and the Ryzen 5 5500 is no exception. It strikes a perfect balance between affordability and performance, making it a solid choice for budget-conscious users who don't want to compromise on power.The installation process was straightforward, and the compatibility with various motherboards adds to the convenience. The bundle also includes some useful software tools that enhance the overall user experience, making it a complete package.While it's not the latest release from AMD, the Ryzen 5 5500 still holds its own in terms of performance, and the bundled extras make it a compelling choice. Overall, I highly recommend the AMD Ryzen 5 5500 6-Core, 12-Thread Unlocked Desktop Processor Bundle to anyone looking for a reliable and cost-effective solution for their computing needs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024

reviews.reviewText: Worked perfectly out of the box as a bundle, as long as you remember it does not come with integrated graphics, and you will need a graphics card to get a display working.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Failure to recognize and boot graphics card.
reviews.reviewText: After hrs of frustration and trouble shooting the mother boars isn't properly working. It will NOT activate the graphics card. 2 different brand new graphics cards were installed on the board in attempt to boot the computer. Both did not boot. And both cards worked fine in a completely separate computer. As part of a controlled experiment and trouble shoot. The board ran every other item but wouldn't let me boot the computer to install windows. Or any other continued set up processes. On most of the forums many people have had similar issues and problems. Aparently it's a bios fault the board will just not move past start up or locate graphics card to give you a screen. To continue install. If it works at a later date then I might change the review. All it's given me is a expensive paperweight.
